# Netlify Edge Functions Environment Variables
# Copy this file to Netlify dashboard -> Site settings -> Environment variables

# Supabase Configuration
SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project-id.supabase.co
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=your-service-role-key-here

# IMPORTANT: 
# - Use the SERVICE ROLE KEY, not the ANON KEY
# - The service role key bypasses RLS policies
# - Never commit this file with real keys to version control
# - Set these in Netlify dashboard for production deployment

# How to get these values:
# 1. Go to https://supabase.com/dashboard
# 2. Select your project
# 3. Go to Settings -> API
# 4. Copy the "URL" (your SUPABASE_URL)
# 5. Copy the "service_role" key (keep this secret!)
